New Records: Travis Head hit a 19-ball fifty in his knock of 59, which included eight fours and four sixes.
Key Match Events: Travis Head provided a rapid start for Australia with a 19-ball fifty.
England stumbled to 52-4 with a batting lineup missing injured captain Jos Buttler.
Liam Livingstone and Sam Curran threatened a fightback with a 54-run partnership for the fifth wicket.
England lost three wickets in 10 balls to plunge to 113-7 and was eventually all out for 151.
Australia's fielding was brilliant, with Tim David's catch to remove Jordan Cox particularly standing out.
Pre-Game Insights: England's lineup included three uncapped players and a stand-in captain in Phil Salt.
England is looking to the future after underwhelming defenses of their 50-over and T20 World Cup titles over the past year.
Post-Match Reflections: Phil Salt reflected on the match, stating, 'Heady came out swinging in the powerplay and gave them a head start but we dragged it back quite nicely in the middle.'
Travis Head commented on his performance, saying, 'I’d love to go out and whack it every time, but I’m in a nice bit of form at the moment and I want to continue that. I’m taking my chances.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia was dismissed for 179 with three balls remaining.
The other matches in the T20 series are in Cardiff on Friday and Manchester on Sunday.
A five-match ODI series between the teams will follow, where Jos Buttler may return from his right calf injury.
